Commentary Text: Ayush Badoni to Suryakumar Yadav, out Caught by Rahul!! Massive wicket as MI lose their best batter this season in Suryakumar! This is drifting across middle and off from round the wicket, and he wants to whip it against the angle over midwicket, probably expecting it to grip a little. Commentary Text: Krunal Pandya to Rohit, out Caught by (sub)Gowtham !! That was a horror shot from Rohit Sharma. Probably sums up Mumbai Indians' season so far. 22 balls since the last boundary and the skipper tries to play the release shot to gather some moment. The intent was good but the execution, exact opposite. A mighty swipe with his body weight falling into the off-side on one knee. Thick top-edge and the fielder at short third had all the time in the world to settle under that. Rohit c (sub)Gowtham b Krunal Pandya 39(31) [4s-5 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Mohsin Khan to Brevis, out Caught by Chameera!! One brings two. Mohsin Khan is pumped up and he has every reason to be so. Bowled it short and wide, Brevis - with both feet up in the air - tried to ramp it fine but didn't quite get the desired timing. Slices it off the thick top-edge and Chameera manages to cling on. It was dipping on him as he ran forward from third man but the pacer never took his eyes off the ball and held his nerve till the last moment. Brevis c Chameera b Mohsin Khan 3(5)

Commentary Text: Ravi Bishnoi to Ishan Kishan, out Caught by Holder!! The torture is over for Ishan Kishan. He started walking even before the bowler broke into half-an-appeal. Probably he had the best sight of that ball and the catch of course. It was a googly from Ravi Bishnoi, Ishan Kishan desperately wanted a release shot and went hard in the process. Skewed it off the thick inside edge and it looped up to the left of Holder at slip straight off the keeper's boot. Holder cannot believe his luck and the LSG players are all smiles. Ishan Kishan c Holder b Ravi Bishnoi 8(20)

Commentary Text: Chameera to Ishan Kishan, no run, did that come straight off the helmet? Looks like it. It appears to have come off the shoulder actually. A mild appeal from LSG, and a shake of the head from umpire Marais Erasmus. Pacy bumper angling across the left-hander, Ishan Kishan swivelled on the pull and took his eyes off momentarily as the ball rips through to hit the shoulder before deflecting towards slip. A brief pause in play as Ishan Kishan takes a hydration break
